The article discusses a recent address by someone at the 45th annual March for Life, in which they called on the Senate to pass the Pain-Capable Unborn Child Protection Act. This legislation aims to protect unborn children who can feel pain at twenty weeks. Despite bipartisan support, the bill was blocked from further consideration. The article argues that this decision goes against scientific evidence and puts the United States out of step with other nations. The author urges the Senate to reconsider and pass legislation that values and protects life.